Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Driver
    Helper class that allows the user to control the robot's movements.
    LightLocalizer
    Light localization class allows the robot to correct its position.
    Main
    Main class of the program.
    Navigation
    Allows the robot to navigate to specific points and push blocks
    ObjectDetection
    Allows the robot to detect objects, avoid them and determine the difference between obstacles.
    Odometer
    The odometer class keeps track of the robot's (x, y, theta) deltaPosition.
    Resources
    Class for static resources (things that stay the same throughout the entire program execution), like constants and hardware.
    Timer
    Class that ensures that simulation runs under given time constraints, and tracks the timeframe throughout which robot conducts operations with respect of team's flowchart and each part of the robot's trajectory
    UltrasonicLocalizer
    Class that reads the ultrasonic sensor data and allows the robot to correct its heading towards 0 when near 2 walls.
